---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { u } from '../../lib/url';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How we work — Thorn Industries"
  description="The principles behind every Thorn Industries engagement. Plain pricing, named accountability, no fragmented contracts, no kickbacks, no surprises."
  lang="en"
>
  <!-- Page header -->
  <section class="container-wide pt-20 pb-12">
    <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-forest-700 font-medium mb-6">How we work</p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink-900 leading-tight mb-6 max-w-3xl">
      The principles every engagement runs on.
    </h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-ink-700 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
      These are not aspirations. They're operating rules. If we can't honour them on a particular engagement, we say so before signing.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Principles -->
  <section class="border-t border-forest-100 py-16">
    <div class="container-wide max-w-4xl space-y-16">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-8">
        <div class="md:col-span-2 text-4xl font-serif text-forest-300 leading-none">01</div>
        <div class="md:col-span-10">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 mb-3">Plain pricing, published ranges</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-700 leading-relaxed">
            Our service pages name the price ranges for every offer. No bespoke quotes hidden until page 40 of a proposal. When we send you a fixed-fee proposal, the numbers will sit inside the published ranges or we'll tell you upfront why this engagement is an exception.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-8">
        <div class="md:col-span-2 text-4xl font-serif text-forest-300 leading-none">02</div>
        <div class="md:col-span-10">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 mb-3">Named accountability, end to end</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-700 leading-relaxed">
            Every engagement has one technical lead. They sign the proposal. They run the discovery. They show up on site. They stay on the project from kickoff to handover. We don't sell you to one team and subcontract delivery to another.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-8">
        <div class="md:col-span-2 text-4xl font-serif text-forest-300 leading-none">03</div>
        <div class="md:col-span-10">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 mb-3">No fragmented contracts</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-700 leading-relaxed">
            Article 11 of Law 98/2016 forbids splitting contracts to dodge procurement thresholds. We won't propose it. If your scope is larger than one threshold, we run the right SEAP procedure for the right size. It takes a few weeks longer. It stays clean.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-8">
        <div class="md:col-span-2 text-4xl font-serif text-forest-300 leading-none">04</div>
        <div class="md:col-span-10">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 mb-3">No kickbacks. No pre-decided tenders.</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-700 leading-relaxed">
            We don't pay to win contracts. We don't participate in tenders that have been decided in advance. If a procurement looks engineered for a specific vendor, we either flag it to ANAP or walk away. This is a hard line, not a slogan.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-8">
        <div class="md:col-span-2 text-4xl font-serif text-forest-300 leading-none">05</div>
        <div class="md:col-span-10">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 mb-3">Open standards, your data stays yours</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-700 leading-relaxed">
            Open formats, exportable schemas, no vendor lock-in clauses. If you ever decide to migrate away from us, we hand you everything that's yours. Code, data, infrastructure-as-code, runbooks. The kind of handover we'd want if we were on your side of the table.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-8">
        <div class="md:col-span-2 text-4xl font-serif text-forest-300 leading-none">06</div>
        <div class="md:col-span-10">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 mb-3">Romanian data residency by default</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-700 leading-relaxed">
            Public-sector data layers run on Romanian infrastructure (Romarg, ClausWeb). Where compute can sit elsewhere without exposing data, we use efficient EU providers (Hetzner) and tell you exactly where each component lives. No mystery, no offshore surprises.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-8">
        <div class="md:col-span-2 text-4xl font-serif text-forest-300 leading-none">07</div>
        <div class="md:col-span-10">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 mb-3">We say what we won't do</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-700 leading-relaxed">
            Each service page has a "what we don't do" section. It's not false modesty. It's the fastest way to make sure both sides know what they're buying. If your problem is outside our scope, we tell you on the first call and, where we can, point you to someone better suited.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-8">
        <div class="md:col-span-2 text-4xl font-serif text-forest-300 leading-none">08</div>
        <div class="md:col-span-10">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 mb-3">Documentation as deliverable</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-700 leading-relaxed">
            Every engagement ships with written documentation: architecture, runbooks, decision log, handover notes. Not because it's nice to have, but because the next person to touch this system needs to understand it without us in the room.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-24 bg-cream-100 border-t border-forest-100">
    <div class="container-wide text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink-900 mb-6 leading-tight">
        These principles sound like a fit?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-ink-600 mb-10">
        Then a conversation is probably worth thirty minutes. Tell us what you're working on.
      </p>
      <a href={u('/en/contact')} class="btn-primary">
        Start a conversation
        <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
